OL,3,CGoing the Extra Mile: The harsh
OL,4,Crealities of a night on the town for
OL,5,Csome
OL,7,F"Oh totally. Even the phrase a night
OL,8,Fin the town. That can mean two
OL,9,Fdifferent things. That can mean going
OL,10,Fout with your friends to party for a
OL,11,FChristmas celebration or a night in
OL,12,Fthe town could means spending the
OL,13,Fnight on the cold pavement stones of
OL,14,Fthis city.... It just brings home the
OL,15,Ftwo tier levels of society," Damian
OL,16,Fsaid.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/7
